rComments: Best prof you can get in a lab ! He is caring and always there for his students ! Highly recommended !

I took his class in 2015 and he did a good job explaining cell regulation. Read the papers BEFORE CLASS and its an easy A+. Hell, all you really need is solid logic!  As long as you can understand an experiment and the interpret the results, you'll pass with flying colors. Also, bring coffee to the lectures!
This is the weirdest, worst prof you can ask for.  There was some rediculous curve on his exams (in the double digits) because he expects way too much for his horrible and rushed style of teaching.
I did not learn anything from this course.
